{"word":"H1340 - בַּת־שׁוּעַ - Bath-Shûwaʻ - bath-shoo'-ah - Bath-shua","slug":"H1340","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בַּת־שׁוּעַ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Bath-Shûwaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>bath-shoo'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bath-shua"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>בּת־שׁוּע</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>bath-shûa‛</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>bath-shoo'-ah</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Bath-shua = \"daughter of wealth\" <ol><li>the wife of Uriah whom David had murdered, having had adulterous relations with her; subsequently wife of David and mother of Solomon, Shimea, Shobab, and Nathan (alternate spelling to 'Bathsheba')</li><li>wife of Judah</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1323\">H1323</a> and <a href=\"#/H7771\">H7771</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Feminine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1121\">H1121</a>, <a href=\"#/H1122\">H1122</a>, <a href=\"#/H1125\">H1125</a>, <a href=\"#/H1126\">H1126</a>, <a href=\"#/H1127\">H1127</a>, <a href=\"#/H1128\">H1128</a>, <a href=\"#/H1130\">H1130</a>, <a href=\"#/H1132\">H1132</a>, <a href=\"#/H1133\">H1133</a>, <a href=\"#/H1134\">H1134</a>, <a href=\"#/H1135\">H1135</a>, <a href=\"#/H1136\">H1136</a>, <a href=\"#/H1139\">H1139</a>, <a href=\"#/H1142\">H1142</a>, <a href=\"#/H1144\">H1144</a>, <a href=\"#/H1145\">H1145</a>, <a href=\"#/H1148\">H1148</a>, <a href=\"#/H1151\">H1151</a>, <a href=\"#/H1323\">H1323</a>, <a href=\"#/H1332\">H1332</a>, <a href=\"#/H1337\">H1337</a>, <a href=\"#/H1339\">H1339</a>, <a href=\"#/H2618\">H2618</a>"}]}